Family Lewis: John Lewis is a soldier fighting for the weakest.
United States Congressman John Lewis, a civil rights fighter, was remembered as a fighter at a memorial service for him on Saturday, 25 July, as “the most vulnerable”.
Lewis' public memorial service has been held in Alabama since Saturday.
There were two memorials on the first day.
On Saturday, at an open memorial service at the University of Troy, Alabama, five brothers and sisters of Lewis and a grandson spoke of him as a loving, fearless and family-oriented man.
Henry “Grand” Lewis, the youngest brother of Lewis, said at the meeting, “He's dedicated his life to helping others.”
Samuel Lewis said that his mother had warned John “Don't get in trouble, don't get in trouble”.
He added that John had not listened to his mother's warning and said, “We all know that John always gets in trouble, always in trouble, but that's because he insists on the right thing, and that's good trouble.”
Lewis' brothers and sisters reminded the people at the memorial that John's most famous argument was to create “good trouble”, that is, not to shy away from provoking things for the sake of justice.
John applied for the University of Troy University, where he was born in the city of Troy, Alabama, but the University of Troy, which was all white schools at that time, refused his application for admission.
As a child, John Lewis, who preached the Gospel on his farm, was awarded a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Many years later, the University of Troy awarded Dr. Lewis an honorary degree.
Congressional Senator Doug Jones from Alabama said that the current protesters were “demonstrating peacefully and in a non-violent manner”, as Lewis had done in the civil rights movement.
According to Jones, “President Trump was wrong even when he knocked over a boat and described all the protesters as thugs.
The protesters are patriots who want the United States to move towards a more equal nation.”
A six-day series of events in honour of Lewis will culminate this week at the funeral in Georgia.
The casket of Lewis was parked on Saturday at a public memorial at the University of Troy, and people came to pay tribute to the leader of the civil rights movement.
Later on Saturday, a private ceremony paid tribute to him in a small church in Selma, Alabama, followed by a public memorial service.
On Sunday, the remains of Lewis will pass through the Edmund Pettus Bridge of Selma.
In 1965, he and the black protesters demanding the right to vote were beaten up by the Alabama State police in front of the bridge, who also gave tear gas to the demonstrators.
Lewis was almost killed.
The day after that was called a bloody Sunday.
The remains of Lewis will be transported to Montgomery, the capital of Alabama.
Mayor Steven Reed encouraged people to line up on the sidewalk and finish this last journey with Lewis.
At the same time, officials require public participation in the event to wear masks and to maintain social distance.
The Governor of Alabama, Kay Ivey, ordered a half-flag to be lowered on Saturdays and Sundays in honour of Lewis.
During the almost week of commemoration, Lewis'remains will be separated from the Alabama State Council Building in Montgomery, the Georgia State Council Building in Atlanta, and the United States Congress Building in Washington, D.C., for public tributes.
Nancy Pelosi, Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, and Mitch McConnell, leader of the Senate Majority Party, announced last week that people could come to the United States Congress Building on Monday and Tuesday to pay tribute to Lewis.
As a result of the coronary virus epidemic, the public event to pay tribute to Lewis will take place outside the house.
Shenzhen's public consultation on the introduction of health regulations - Xinhuanet
On 26 July, Shenzhen Xinhua (journalist Maussing, White Yo) encouraged residents to perform medical examinations on a regular basis and to detect problems at an early stage; prohibited the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; set up a health screening system for online games; and had to be staffed with part-time health managers... The Health Regulations of the Shenzhen Special Economic Zone (Consultation Draft) had been officially published, and the Shenzhen residents would have their own “health laws”.
In order to encourage residents to undergo medical examinations and to identify problems at an early stage, it was suggested that the health services should develop a basic catalogue of health check-ups based on age, occupation, etc.
The cost of a health check-up, which falls within the basic catalogue of health-care projects, is covered by the Integrated Fund for Social Health Insurance at the rate of one per person per year.
It is clear from the comments that the employer should make a reasonable allocation of human resources, make staff time available, introduce a rotation system for workers with higher mental and physical workloads, avoid excessive loss of human capacity or physical or mental health damage to the health of the employee, and enforce the system of paid leave for employees.
In addition, employers are required to have dedicated part-time health managers and to organize regular staff health check-ups.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the consultation draft proposed that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors should be prohibited and that the location of the sale of alcoholic beverages should be restricted. In the event of a violation of the regulations, a fine of 30,000 yuan would be imposed on the management of the market.
In addition to the Prohibition of Liquor, minors also have to be “multi-opportunity”.
According to the consultation draft, schools are required to arrange for physical activity for more than one hour per day.
In the case of cyber games, the public security, cultural wide-television sports, network supervision and health departments should improve the system of health supervision of Internet Internet service establishments and establish a system of health screening for online games in order to create a good space for interaction and a culture of interaction in order to promote the healthy development of young people.
In addition, the consultation notes that patients with influenza are required to wear masks to access public places and that health-care institutions are fined $20,000, etc. for leaking patients'privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of the population, the consultation draft also requires the Shenzhen sector to assess the impact of the implementation of public policies on the health of the population prior to the preparation of plans relating to urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource exploitation and environmental protection, the development of the biomedical industry, normative documents and the approval of major construction projects and the implementation of major public service projects.
It may not be enacted or approved for implementation without an assessment or assessment that would have a more serious adverse effect on urban public health or the health of the population.
