Adequate sleep can relax the brain and the entire body system, both for work and learning and as a preventive measure against heat and heat.
According to the experts, the best time to go to bed was between 2200 and 2300 hours, and the best time to get up was between 5.30 and 6.30 p.m.
While sleeping, be careful not to lie under air conditioning vents and electric fans in order to develop air conditioners and hot wind.
