The 26-day-long-long, three-thousand tunnel is a full-line control project for Cheng Wangong Iron. The project is located on the border between Chongqing and Sooshan counties. It is approximately 18.9 km long and is buried at a maximum depth of 890 metres.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and became fully operational on 26 July 2020.
According to the Royal Army, the director of the design of the Chinese Iron II Engineering Group of China, Cheng Wan Gao Tunnel, the company limited in responsibility for the exploration of the design, the geologic conditions of the location of the San Gorge Tunnel are very complex and exposed to the risks of rock solubility, mud pouring water, and large-scale deformation of soft rock, which are high-risk tunnels of level I, and whose design and construction are extremely difficult.
