Before volunteering, find out what a professional is-- a new network.
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning newspaper
Before volunteering, you'll have to figure out what a professional is.
Each year, students or parents report to the NCC because they are not aware of the terminology involved in the voluntary filing, which in turn affects the voluntary filing.
This year, the Beijing Transport University, the Beijing University of Science and Technology, the Beijing Post and Telecommunications University, the Beijing Forestry University, the Beijing Chemical University and five higher schools jointly launched a 2020 admission policy to eliminate professional differentials.
What is the significance of professional underperformance in voluntary filings?
There are three ways of assigning a profession.
Experts cautioned that before volunteering, it was important to have a detailed reading of the Statute of Admission to Heart School and to have an understanding of the rules governing admission to higher education, including the percentage of placements, the rules for the allocation of professions, etc.
The rules for the assignment of specialties refer to the three main forms of professional priority, merit priority and professional differentials for admission to the profession after a post-secondary grade.
The specific modalities used by universities will be specified in the Statute of Admissions.
However, there are also some institutions of higher education where the principle of overall priority is given, with no difference in level between specializations.
This means that candidates within the range of admission are queued on the basis of the total score, and when the score does not reach the first professional voluntary entry score line, it depends on whether the second professional voluntary entry score line is reached, and so on until the last professional volunteer is admitted, with no difference in rank between professional volunteers.
The so-called “professional difference” is the value of one or more of the points published in the admission charters for the selection of candidates for the different specializations, which is the “professional gap”.
That is to say, the difference in the scores of students enrolled in the colleges in the first and non-first professions, and the difference in the grades among the various professions, e.g., 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
It is assumed that Ming, a student, will take a 560-point course in higher education: computers, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, and that the admission of students to higher education A will be based on a professional grade differential of 2 points, 1 point, 1 point and 0 points.
In the case of professional assignments, if the junior professional volunteer meets the requirements for professional admission and has a planned professional balance, the junior professional is admitted to the “computer” profession; if the computer is not accepted, his score is subtracted by two points, ranking 558 points as candidates for the “international trade” examination of the first professional volunteer, determining whether the qualification is met; if it is still not met, the third professional voluntary “automated” entry is reduced by one point (i.e., 557); if it is still not met, the next professional entry is reduced by one point (i.e., 556) for the fourth professional, and if it is still unable to meet its professional volunteering, no less, and so on.
Different university-level differentials.
With the spread of parallel volunteering, many higher education institutions have now eliminated their professional grades, but some of them have retained this method this year, with more than 20 universities having established their professional grades, according to the Charter of Admissions published by the respective schools.
For example, the Sichuan University of Agriculture, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Teacher University, Chengdu Medical School, Northeast Electric University, American University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing Industrial University, Ningxia University, Shandong Technical University, Chinese Institute of Civil Aviation Flight, etc.
In these universities, the professional differentials are different for each university.
Some institutions of higher education have a grade difference in each field, such as the University of Ningxia, where the files have been sent to candidates, in order of reduction of one point in the order in which candidates report their professional volunteers.
Some universities, on the other hand, set different levels of specialization between different specializations.
For example, at the University of the United States of America, the total margin for professional volunteer grades is 4 points, i.e. 3 points for first-professional volunteers and 3 points for other professional volunteers, no grade differentials between other professional volunteers, which are considered to be parallel voluntary, and 1 point for other professional and transfer professional volunteers.
When volunteering, candidates and parents must take a careful look at the admission policies of the schools they report, see if there are any differences in specialization, what the forms of differences are, and, while taking the scores fully into account, make a sound analysis of the schools and professions to be selected. If the admission rules of the institutions are explicitly based on differential grades, when selecting a profession, the candidates must pay attention to the gradient between the professions and increase the rate of admission.
