The police stopped people from "seeming too happy" when the Chengdu came together to watch the consulate.
In response to the closure of the Chinese Consulate General in Houston, China announced the closure of the United States Consulate General in Chengdu this Friday.
On Saturday, the emblem of the United States Consulate was withdrawn and on Sunday, a dark glass car left the Consulate in the noise of passers-by.
On Sunday, a lot of Chengdu people were standing in front of the United States Consulate to take photographs, and people who had not been here had come to see them, driven by curiosity.
Agence France-Presse (Agence France-Presse) station journalists also observed a number of times near the Consulate in Chengdu, reporting that people were curious and that there were many parents who took their children for walks to the Consulate, photographed the building or photographed themselves.
The consulate was surrounded by guards who seemed not to allow any appearance: a woman had been stopped just after she had begun to sing a red song, and a guard had confiscated a banner.
But the inhabitants of a nearby residential building succeeded in lifting a giant Chinese flag from their balcony and chanting slogans in support of China.
The Chengdu Consulate opened in 1985 to cover all consular-related matters of the United States in south-west China, in particular the Tibet Autonomous Region.
Agence France-Presse journalist said that the Chinese Government's response to the United States was relatively restrained: a large number of Chinese online demanded that the United States Consulate in Hong Kong be closed, but the official simply said that “the closure of the Consulate in Chengdu was a necessary and legitimate response to the United States' unreasonable conduct”.
At present, in addition to Chengdu, the United States is based in Guangdong, Shanghai, Shenyang, Wuhan and the Consulate of Hong Kong.
We're on the move for a large-scale integrated media campaign called "Living Village Lives to End Poverty" - and today's highlights - the Hunan Daily News Network - We're on-line.
On 25 July, two caravans carrying a 5G mobile cloud broadcasting system were delivered by guests from Jiangsu Xu Xuzhou, under the auspices of the Central Radio and Television Central Finance and Economics Centre.
According to Xi Jinping, “The year 2020 will be a landmark year in which we will achieve the full realization of a small and prosperous society, the first century of struggle, and the year 2020 will be the year of decisive victory in the fight against poverty”.
The large-scale integrated media campaign " Villages live to see out of poverty " is an important initiative of the Central Radio and Television Finance Centre to complement this major theme in its campaign against poverty.
It will enter the poverty-eradication villages of more than 20 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the central authority of the country, digging for stories of living out of poverty, confronting the dramatic changes in the village and showing how the villagers have managed to break through the path of survival and development and move towards prosperity.
The operation will last for more than three months.
From Xuzhou, the journalists travelled along the south-west line, via Anhui, Hubei, Jiangxi, Hunan, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Chongqing, Yunnan, Tibet, etc., and the north-west route, via Henan, Shaanxi, Gansu, Qinghai, Xinjiang, Ningxia, Neo-Mongolia, Shanxi and Hebei, over 10,000 kilometres.
In the form of the coverage, the Village Live to see Poverty Out was boldly integrated.
The economic developments in the villages to which the caravan arrived will be aired through the Central Radio and Television General Television (CRT) TV channel, the Yangang Economic Voice, China Transport Broadcasting, and the new financial media.
Of these, live television coverage will be completed in the midday news programme, The Economy of the World, primarily by the Finance Channel (first air time: Monday to Sunday, 12 noon to 13 p.m.), and a special section on combating poverty will be set up in the Golden News section, Economic Information Network, of the Finance Channel (first air time: Monday to Sunday, 20:30 to 21:30).
At the same time, caravans will be broadcast live for up to one hour in each of the villages visited by viewing financial transactions on the client side, and the audience will be able to view them by downloading the financial transactions APP and participating in the drawings.
In technology applications and studio design, Village Live to see Poverty Out, the first of its kind, was the “New Media Caravan for Outer Space”.
The vehicle was equipped with a 5G-new media mobile cloud system, using 5G+4K/8K+AI technology to bring about an organic combination of online, big screens and television broadcasts.
It is equipped with a three-stage broadcast area, which is modified from containers 12 metres long, 2.55 metres wide and 3.98 metres high, with a hydraulic self-dismantling structure with a maximum capacity of 120 degrees up.
The broadcast area can also be automatically opened and extended outside the platform, covering more than 50 square metres, to meet most of the programme's scenario requirements.
The present area of Dongchuan in Kunming City is already inflamed by summer, while more hot than the weather is the easy relocation of anti-poverty workshops near settlement sites.
“Now, as soon as you leave the house, you go to the factory and make money, thanks to free vocational skills training organized by the trade unions.”
A hot, busy picture of the situation in the east of the country entered a workshop for the processing of electronic components of the copper street in the eastern part of the city.
Lüling, aged over 40, is a single mother with children and also takes care of elderly parents.
At her most difficult time, the Eastkawa Regional General Trade Union helped to figure out a way to “show charcoal in the snow” after running.
Since 2018, Lu Ling has benefited from housing, schooling, social security, employment, etc., and benefits from various trade unions.
This year, her child was successfully graduated and employed, and she herself was able to work and earn an income after participating in skills training and was released at the end of April.
According to the information received, a special skills training project of the Eastkawa Region General Organization to help fight poverty is part of the skills training of the Yunnan Province General Union.
In conjunction with the characteristics of the disadvantaged workers in the relocation centres in the region, an in-depth survey was carried out to identify training needs and types of training, and a total of 450 electricians, welders, face-pointers, etc. were scheduled to be trained in the near future.
In recent days, Li Yi, a staff member of the Yunnan Monjan County branch of the agricultural bank, wrote a heartfelt letter of thanks to the county trade union.
In her letter, she expressed her sincere gratitude to the trade union for giving her a study grant in Kim Autu between August 2013 and January 2017 to help her complete her studies.
In 2004, Li Yi's father died in a car accident and the mother was included in the files of the workers in need, and has since benefited from the establishment of the card-setting policy.
With the help of local trade unions, Li Yi successfully completed her studies.
Since 2016, 3809 families have been released through institutional safeguards and precision support.
The successful release of the Lülin family and Li Yi is a microcosm of the Yunnan trade union's push for the relief of workers in need.
According to the Chief Executive Officer of the General Union of Yunnan, the Ministry of Law and Defence of Rights Department, the department has been strengthening the dynamic management of the files of workers in difficulty, promoting the regularization of the construction work and the timely integration into the support system of workers in need who meet the requirements for filing; expanding the channels for applying to workers in need; and using micro-letters to open up online a filing service platform for workers in difficulty to facilitate the timely and voluntary declaration of workers in need.
During the period of the epidemic, it was difficult to work outside the country and, in order to help people in difficult circumstances ease the stress of their lives, Yunnan Province had set aside a total of more than 13 million yuan for the provision of warm funds for the provision of warm condolences to more than 6,000 families in difficult circumstances at the national level and 1,000 families in difficult circumstances at the provincial level, in accordance with the standard of 1,500 yuan per household for workers in difficult circumstances at the national level and at the provincial level.
At the same time, various Internet recruitment platforms, such as the Department of Social Welfare and IUPU recruitment, are being connected, and recruitment information is being sent to workers in need, and services such as employment counselling and guidance are being provided.
